def: To reduce to method; to dispose in due order; to arrange in aconvenient manner; as, to methodize one's work or thoughts.Spectator.
A voyage; a journey. [Obs.] Chaucer. Gower.
Capable of being paralleled, or equaled. [R.] Bp. Hall.
The quality or state of being tepid; moderate warmth;lukewarmness; tepidness. Jer. Taylor.
A European fish (Box vulgaris), having a compressed body andbright colors; -- called also box, and bogue.

A pencil of carbon used in producing electric light. Crayonboard, cardboard with a surface prepared for crayon drawing.-- Crayon drawing, the act or art of drawing with crayons; a drawingmade with crayons.
One of the Gallinae or gallinaceous birds.
A narrow and elongated aperture; a cleft; a fissure.
To move with a lever; to force up or open; to pry. [Writtenalso prise.]
